children.text: The external ceiling area has not been properly fastened to the ceiling members with fixings at the correct centres to prevent the ceiling from failure.
The Victorian Building Authority’s Guide to Standards and Tolerances states in section 9.11 Plasterboard Sheeting, that
‘The installation and jointing of plasterboard sheeting systems is defective if it does not conform to AS/NZS 2589 and the manufacturer’s installation instructions’ .
The plasterboard manufacturer in their installation instructions state in their ‘Installation of External Ceilings’ section that

‘Spacing between framing members should not exceed the maximum values indicated in Table 22. In areas where these values are exceeded, suitable ceiling battens or furring channels should be provided at required spacings’
‘At sheet ends space screws at 300mm maximum centres for cornices and 150mm maximum centres for square set finish’
‘Ceiling linings should be fully screw fixed at maximum spacings indicated in Table 22’
The builder must install additional trimmer and/or fasteners at 300mm centres along the battens or trimmers spaced at 450mm centres, in accordance with the manufacturer’s requirements.
